description: Number of partitions of n into parts of 17 kinds.
comments: a(n) is Euler transform of A010856. - _Alois P. Heinz_, Oct 17 2008
links: Alois P. Heinz, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..1000
Index entries for expansions of Product_{k >= 1} (1-x^k)^m
maple: with(numtheory): a:= proc(n) option remember; `if`(n=0, 1, add(add(d*17, d=divisors(j)) *a(n-j), j=1..n)/n) end: seq(a(n), n=0..40); # _Alois P. Heinz_, Oct 17 2008
crossrefs: Cf. 17th column of A144064. - _Alois P. Heinz_, Oct 17 2008
